# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# LOCAL DEVELOPMENT (client-side, prefixed with VITE_)
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# These variables are used when running `npm run dev` locally.
# The app calls the AI API directly from the browser.

# ─── OPTION A (Recommended): Groq — FREE, fast, OpenAI-compatible ───
# Sign up at https://console.groq.com and create a free API key.
VITE_AI_API_KEY=gsk_your-groq-key-here
VITE_AI_BASE_URL=https://api.groq.com/openai/v1
VITE_AI_MODEL=llama-3.3-70b-versatile

# ─── OPTION B: Google Gemini — FREE tier, OpenAI-compatible ────────
# Get a key at https://aistudio.google.com/apikey
# VITE_AI_API_KEY=your-google-ai-key
# VITE_AI_BASE_URL=https://generativelanguage.googleapis.com/v1beta/openai
# VITE_AI_MODEL=gemini-2.0-flash

# ─── OPTION C: OpenAI — PAID ──────────────────────────────────────
# Get a key at https://platform.openai.com/api-keys
# VITE_AI_API_KEY=sk-your-openai-key
# VITE_AI_BASE_URL=https://api.openai.com/v1
# VITE_AI_MODEL=gpt-4o-mini

# ─── OPTION D: OpenRouter — some models are free ──────────────────
# Get a key at https://openrouter.ai/keys
# VITE_AI_API_KEY=your-openrouter-key
# VITE_AI_BASE_URL=https://openrouter.ai/api/v1
# VITE_AI_MODEL=meta-llama/llama-3.3-70b-instruct:free

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# VERCEL / PRODUCTION (server-side, NOT prefixed with VITE_)
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Set these in the Vercel dashboard under Project Settings → Environment Variables.
# The serverless function at api/recommend.js uses these to call the AI
# server-side, keeping the key out of client-side bundles.
#
# AI_API_KEY=gsk_your-groq-key-here
# AI_BASE_URL=https://api.groq.com/openai/v1
# AI_MODEL=llama-3.3-70b-versatile

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# HOW ROUTING WORKS
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# • If VITE_AI_API_KEY is set → browser calls the AI API directly (local dev)
# • If VITE_AI_API_KEY is NOT set → browser calls /api/recommend proxy (Vercel)
# This switch is automatic; no code changes needed.
